Mars is sometimes called the Red Planet. It's red because of rusty iron in the ground. Like Earth, Mars has seasons, polar ice caps, volcanoes, canyons, and weather. It has a very thin atmosphere made of carbon dioxide, nitrogen, and argon.Mars is also known as the Red Planet. ...
Mars is named after the Roman god of war.
Mars has 2 moons called Deimos and Phobos. ...
Mars is the 4th planet from the sun. ...
Mars is smaller than Earth with a diameter of 4217 miles.

